1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:02,291
My name is Aladdin Khaled Ahmad

2
00:00:02,875 --> 00:00:04,541
I am from the Nabi Jirjis area

3
00:00:04,791 --> 00:00:06,875
I was born in 1973

4
00:00:08,375 --> 00:00:12,916
ISIS detained me over a medicines case

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,791
I stayed in this place 28 days

6
00:00:20,166 --> 00:00:22,625
And 10 days in another place

7
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:29,041
The medicines were for chronic illnesses

8
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:30,458
They were not sold in pharmacies

9
00:00:31,291 --> 00:00:33,875
When they exceeded what the recipients needed

10
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,375
They brought them to me, knowing I distributed to those in need

11
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:41,166
Things like that

12
00:00:43,625 --> 00:00:44,791
I was under surveillance

13
00:00:45,041 --> 00:00:46,625
I felt I was being watched

14
00:00:47,125 --> 00:00:50,416
Because they were sending women to my store

15
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:56,250
For medicines, and I gave injections to people for free

16
00:00:58,166 --> 00:01:01,375
Interviewer: Were the women they sent from among their members?

17
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:03,333
Yes, members of ISIS

18
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:07,166
Interviewer: Did you learn that from them, or later?

19
00:01:07,333 --> 00:01:08,333
I learned later

20
00:01:09,291 --> 00:01:12,333
After they detained me

21
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:17,791
I only had a feeling that they were the ones sending them

22
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:21,041
ISIS, and that was why I was detained

23
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:23,541
Interviewer: What was the source of the medicines that came to you?

24
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:25,541
It was from people who had more than they needed

25
00:01:25,625 --> 00:01:27,541
Yes, from people who wanted to do good

26
00:01:27,666 --> 00:01:29,875
Interviewer: Were there people who bought medicines

27
00:01:29,916 --> 00:01:32,416
Interviewer: And brought them to you seeking a reward for that?
Witness: Yes

28
00:01:33,041 --> 00:01:35,041
Interviewer: Did that happen with you?
Witness: Yes, it happened

29
00:01:36,166 --> 00:01:39,250
I used to work in a pharmacy

30
00:01:39,875 --> 00:01:41,375
So people in the area knew me

31
00:01:42,208 --> 00:01:44,458
They told anyone who wanted to donate, Take it to Abu Abd al-Rahman

32
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,250
He is a man who does good for people

33
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:49,000
So this was a trust I passed on seeking reward

34
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:52,333
I wanted to do good—I did not sell them
